    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Montreal</placeName>
                <date>3d March 5620</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sirâ€”</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">I received a message<lb/> per <persName>Sarah Joseph</persName>
                which makes me<lb/> think you misunderstood what<lb/> I wrote about <persName>Dr
                    Dawson's</persName> book.<lb/> She writes me you said you cannot<lb/> notice the
                book until you had<lb/> seen it. I thought the<lb/> article already in the
                Occident<lb/> notice enough. I requested her<lb/> to inform you that I was<lb/>
                writing a Review of it for<lb/> a medical journal here. The<lb/> first part appeared
                in <date>Feby</date> and<lb/> I am now correcting the proof of the</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>last. When it is printed off I<lb/> shall send you a copy of it.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Did you not also<lb/> misunderstand about sending<lb/> the Occident
                to <persName>Dr D.</persName> I asked<lb/> you to send a copy (extra)<lb/>
                containing the notice of his work,<lb/> &amp; you appear to have understood<lb/>
                that I asked you to continue sending him a copy. <persName>Dr D.</persName> is<lb/>
                such a busy man, and so<lb/> thoroughly devoted to science<lb/> that he has little
                or rather<lb/> no time for theology. I never<lb/> knew a man who does as<lb/> much
                as he does, and with<lb/> such readiness &amp; little effort.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Your venture is getting<lb/> near its end. Do you</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>intend to change its form.<lb/> I believe that the old form<lb/> would be much
                preferred<lb/> none here like it as it is.<lb/> Many have the monthly bound.<lb/>
                The <hi rend="underline">other</hi>
                <sic>weeklys</sic> are never<lb/> preserved.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">How gets on the Board of Delegates. What a <hi rend="underline"
                    >powerful</hi><lb/> reply to <persName>Einhorn</persName> appears<lb/> in the
                Messenger. It would<lb/> read well in the Herald<lb/> on t'other side
                    <persName>Einhorns</persName> article.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I must close, as the<lb/> party who has promised to<lb/> take a few
                lines for me<lb/> is about to start. Vale.</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">Yours truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">
                <persName role="author">Abraham de Sola</persName>
            </p>
            <p>Did you see</p>
            <p>notice of <persName>Dr R</persName></p>
            <p><persName>Chief Rabbi</persName> of</p>
            <p><placeName>N. Y.</placeName> in <persName>Frank Littles</persName> paper?</p>
        </body>
